    "checklist_browser_mirror": "Quick checklist:\n• Sigil desktop is running on this PC.\n• Browser source URL matches Curses: <code>http://localhost:PORT/client</code> (use the port shown in Sigil; Copy in the OBS tab fills this in).\n• The active scene has at least one Text element; set its text source (e.g. Speech-to-Text).\n• In OBS, turn off “Shutdown source when not visible” if updates freeze when the source is hidden.",
    "native_captions_explain": "With WebSocket connected, Native stream captions send your chosen text source to OBS via SendStreamCaption (stream-embedded captions). No browser source is required for that path.",
    "browser_source_desc": "Create new browser source, paste the link and set window size to {{width}}x{{height}} pixels",
    "browser_source_tips": "OBS uses an embedded browser (CEF), not your installed Chrome. If the URL works in Chrome/Edge but not in OBS, update OBS, enable Settings → Advanced → “Enable browser source hardware acceleration”, then right‑click the browser source → Refresh.\nThe local server follows the original Curses setup: use <code>http://localhost:PORT/client</code> (same as Curses’ <code>localhost:3030/client</code> with your port).\nKeep Sigil running while streaming.\nAdd a Text element on the canvas for the active scene if you expect visible captions.\nIn OBS, turn off “Shutdown source when not visible” if the source freezes when hidden.",
